<section id="aligned-form" class="container">

		<h3>Aligned Form</h3>
		<p>Each form field is displayed on a separate line, with the field labels aligned to the left of the field.  The buttons are displayed below the form on a separate line.</p>
		<p>One issue with aligned forms is that they do not scale well to small screen sizes. To overcome that it is usually good practice to default the mobile view to block style and then enhance large screens with align mode using a media query.</p>

		<div class="example">

			<form>

				<fieldset>

					<legend>Account Information</legend>

					<div class="field">
						<label>Email:</label>
						<input type="email" placeholder="user@domain.com" required />
						<span class="hint">Email address is required and must be in the format: user@@domain.com</span>
					</div>

					<div class="field">
						<label>Password:</label>
						<input type="password" placeholder="Password" required />
						<span class="hint">Password is required</span>
					</div>

